"Varje projekt kan innehГҘlla en eller flera ordlistor som en fГ¶rkortning fГ¶r "
"lagring av terminologi. Ordlistor hjГӨlper till att upprГӨtthГҘlla konsekvensen "
"i Г¶versГӨttningen."

#: user/glossary.rst:9
msgid ""
"A glossary for each language can be managed on its own, but they are stored "
"together as a single component which helps project admins and multilingual "
"translators to maintain some cross-language consistency as well. Terms from "
"the glossary containing words from the currently translated string are "
"displayed in the sidebar of the translation editor."
msgstr ""
"En ordlista fГ¶r varje sprГҘk kan hanteras separat, men de lagras tillsammans "
"som en enda komponent, vilket hjГӨlper projektadministratГ¶rer och "
"flersprГҘkiga Г¶versГӨttare att upprГӨtthГҘlla en viss sprГҘkГ¶vergripande "
"konsistens. Termer frГҘn ordlistan som innehГҘller ord frГҘn den aktuella "
"Г¶versatta strГӨngen visas i sidofГӨltet i Г¶versГӨttningsredigeraren."

#: user/glossary.rst:17
msgid ""
"The glossary terms are not used in quality checks unless you enable that, "
"see :ref:`check-check-glossary` for more information."
msgstr ""
"Ordlistan anvГӨnds inte i kvalitetskontroller om du inte aktiverar den. "
"Se :ref:`check-check-glossary` fГ¶r mer information."

#: user/glossary.rst:21
msgid "Managing glossaries"
msgstr "Hantera ordlistor"

#: user/glossary.rst:25
msgid ""
"Glossaries are now regular translation components and you can use all "
"Weblate features on them вҖ” commenting, storing in a remote repository, or "
